Build the number "7" out of the available blocks. First, start with the #1 cube. Place it in the upper lefthand side of the table. Place the #2 cube to the immediate right of the #1 cube. Place the #3 to the right of the #2. Move the #4 cube to the right of the #3. Position the #5 directly right of the #4 cube. Place the #7 to the right of the #5. Move the #12 to the right of the #7. Place the #16 to the right of the #12. The #17 will be moved to the position directly below the #16. Move the #18 below the #17. Position the #13 directly below the #18. Now, slide the #13, one cube-space to the left. Move the #14 to the position directly below the #13. Move the #15 directly below the #14. Move the #8 to the position directly left of the #15. Place the #9 beneath the #8. Place the #10 below the #9. Move the #11 to the position below the #10. Finally, place the #6 in the position directly left of the #11.

Create the formation of a number "7" using all the available cubes.
First, create a horizontal line near the top of the table, using the following eight blocks in the order listed: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 12, 16. Now place the 17 below the 16, followed by the 18 below the 17. Move the 13 below the 18. Now, slide the 13, one cube-space to the left. Place the 14 below the 13 and the 15 below the 14. now place the 8 directly left the 15. Move the 9 below the 8, the 10 below the 9 and the 11 below the 10. Finally move the 6 directly left the 11.

Using all the available cubes, create a picture of the number 7 using the following directions:

First, create a horizontal line across the top of the table using the following eight cubeds in sequence: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 12, and 16. Second, place the 17 below the 16 and the 18 below the 17. Third, place the 13 to the position directly left the 18 and slide it down one cube-space. Move the 14 below the 13 and the 15 below the 14. Now, place the 8 directly left the 15. Move the 9 to the position beneath the 8, the 10 below the 9 and the 11 beneath the 10. Finally, move the 6 to the position directly left the 11.

Start by making a 2x2 square in the center of the table. The top row has 8 and 12; the bottom row has 9 and 13. Next make a 4x3 rectangle without its corners. You will be making an 8 with the blocks. Start with the top loop. Make two rows near the top of the board with two block lengths between them. Place 6 and 10 in a row going right starting below and to the right of 2. Place 14 and 18 above and to the right of 10. Place 13 to the right of   9. You're all done!

We will make an oblong shape starting clock wise. First we build the right vertical line of our shape composed of five blocks: 16, 17, 18, 19, and 20, in a descending fashion. Next we make a diagonal line going down and to the left of 20 with three blocks: 15, 13, and 11. To the left of 11 we form our bottom base with two more blocks: 9 and then 7 respectively.  Next we make an ascending vertical line. The start block will be one up and to the left of 7 and that block is 5. Going upwards we build 5, 4, 3, 2, then 1. Next we going in a diagonal fashion from 1 going up and to the right with 6, 8, 10 and then 12. Lastly place block 14 one down and to the right of 12 and it should connect with 16 completing our shape.

We will make an oblong shape in a counter-clockwise fashion. First start with 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5 in a descending vertical line downward with 1 on top. Next place 7 one down and to the right of 5. One down and to the right of 5 is our bottom base line composed of  7, 9, and 11 from left to right.  Forming a diagonal line going up and to the right are blocks 13, 15, and 20. Next we build an ascending vertical line starting above block 20. We build upwards with 19, 18, 17, and 16. Our next diagonal line going two blocks up and to the left will be respectively placed with 14 and 12. For clarity, 12 should be at the top of our structure. Lastly, in a diagonal line going down and to the left from 12, we place 10, then 8, and then 6. 6 should be one space up and to the right of block 1. This will complete our oblong.

We will build an oblong shape with the blocks available to us. First we will make the vertical lines. Take blocks 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5 and build them in a descending fashion with block 1 at the top. Next, six square spaces to the right of 3, we place block 20 and build in an ascending fashion starting with 20. We place 19, 18, 17 and then 16 to form our last vertical line in our structure. For our only horizontal line, we start by placing 7 one space down and to the right of 5. To the right of 7 we place 9 and then 11 forming our bottom base line. Next we place a diagonal line one space up and to the right of 11 with blocks 13 and 15. This will connect our bottom half of our structure. Next, going one space up and to the right of block 1, we make another diagonal line with blocks 6, 8, 10, and 12. Our last block, 14, will be place one space down and to the right of 12. For clarity, 14 should be one space up and to the left of block 16. This will complete our oblong construction.

We will build a slanted oblong shape with number blocks. For the first part we will take 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 and place them in a descending vertical line fashion in that order. 1 will be at the top. To the right of 6 we place two blocks: 8 and then 10. We build a diagonal line going up and to the right from block 10. It is of three blocks, 12, 14, and 20. Above 20 is another ascending vertical line made of these numbers respectively: 19, 18, 17, 16, and 15. Next place 13 and 11 respectively to the left of 15 to form the top base line of the oblong. Lastly in a diagonal line going down and to the left, put 9 and then 7. Block 7 should be one above and to the right of block 1 where we started. This finishes our oblong shape.

We will build an oblong shape in a counter-clockwise fashion. Starting the top base line of the form, we take 11, then 13, and 15 going left to right forming a horizontal line. Under 15 is a descending vertical line of 5 more blocks: 16, 17, 18, 19, and then 20. A diagonal line going down and to the left from 20 are three blocks: 14, 12, and 10. From the left of 10 is the bottom base line of our oblong: 8 and 6 respectively. Above 6 is another ascending vertical line composed of five more blocks: 5, 4, 3, 2, and 1. Lastly, a diagonal line going up and to the right of 1 are our last two blocks: 7 and then 9. For clarity, 9 should be one space below and to the left of 11. This will form our oblong shaped building.

For our oblong shape we will build with the blocks we have. First take 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6, and put them respectively in a descending vertical line fashion. Then square spaces to the right of 3 we will make an ascending vertical line composed of six more blocks: 20, 19, 18, 17, 16, and 15 respectively placed in that order. We will then put the horizontal lines. To the right of 6 and 8 and 10 respectively forming the bottom base. To the right of 15 are 13 and then 11 respectively forming the top base. Next we have a diagonal line from 20 going down and to the left with blocks 14 and 12. 12 should be one up and to the right of 10. Lastly we make our last diagonal line of 7 and 9. 7 should be one up and to the right 1 and 9 should be one down and to the left of 11. This will finish our oblong shape.

You will be making a 2 with the blocks. First start on the base. Place UPS, Toyota, and Stella Artois in a line starting two blocks to the left and two blocks above the bottom right table corner. Start by making two rows of three blocks each with the right block one block higher on the table than the left row. The right row has (starting from the right) UPS, Toyota, and Stella Artois. The lower left row has Shell, Mercedes Benz, and Heineken. Move Burger King so it is above and to the left of Heineken. Next, make a diagonal across the center of the table. It starts above Burger King and has BMW, Esso, McDonalds, and Pepsi. Next add an backwards L made out of diagonal blocks. The base starts to the right of Pepsi and has Starbucks, Texaco, and Twitter. The side has Twitter, Target, and SRI. Move Nvidia so it is to the left of SRI. Lastly add another row starting below and to the left of Nvidia. The blocks to use are HP, Coca Cola, and Adidas. The final pattern should be a number 2.

You'll be making a numeral 2 out of blocks. First start with the top. Place Adidas and Coca Cola in a row near the top of the table. Place HP and Nvidia in a diagonal going up and to the right starting right of Coca Cola. Place SRI, Target, and Twitter in a diagonal going down and to the right starting right of Nvidia. Next work on the diagonal of the 2. Place Texaco below and to the left of Twitter. Place Starbucks and Pepsi in a row going left starting below and to the left of Texaco. Place McDonalds, Esso, and BMW below and to the left of Pepsi. Lastly work on the base of the 2. Place Burger King and Heineken in a diagonal going down and to the right starting below BMW. Place Mercedes Benz and Shell to the right of Heineken. Place Stella Artois, Toyota, and UPS in a row going right starting above and to the right of Shell. You're all done!

BMW, Esso, McDonalds, and Pepsi are in a northeast line in the center of the table. Starbucks, Texaco, and Twitter are in a northeast line starting east of Pepsi. Target is northwest of Twitter. SRI and Nvidia are in a row going west starting northwest of Target. HP, Coca Cola, and Adidas are in a row going west starting southwest of Nvidia. Burger King is south of BMW. Heineken, Mercedes Benz, and Shell are in a row going east starting southeast of Burger King. Stella Artois, Toyota, and UPS are in a row going east starting northeast of Shell. Congratulations, you've made the number 2 out of blocks!

We will build a curvy two shaped structure. From left to right: Adidas, Coca-Cola, and HP. One space up and to the right place Nvidia. Put SRI to the right of Nvidia. Diagonal line one space down and to the right we put Target then Twitter. One space down and to the left we place Texaco. A horizontal line going right to left starting one space down and to the left of Texaco are Starbucks then Pepsi. Next is a diagonal line going down and to the left from Pepsi is McDonalds, Esso, then BMW. Below BMW is Burger King. We build a horizontal line from left to right starting one space down and to the right from Burger King with Heineken, Mercedes-Benz, then Shell. One space up and to the right from Shell we finish our last horizontal line going left to right: Stella Artois, Toyota, then UPS.

We will build a curvy two shaped structure with the blocks. From right to left: UPS, Toyota, then Stella Artois. One space down and to the left from Stella Artois going right to left horizontally are Shell, Mercedes-Benz, and then Heineken. Next one space up and to the left from Heineken is Burger King with BMW above it. Next we form diagonal line going up to the right from BMW with Esso, McDonalds, then Pepsi. To the right of Pepsi is Starbucks. We build a diagonal line going up to the right from Starbucks with Texaco, then Twitter. Next another diagonal line going up to the left from Twitter with Target then SRI. To the left of SRI is Nvidia. Lastly we make a horizontal line going right to left one space down and to the left from Nvidia with HP, then Coca-Cola, and then Adidas. This completes our building.

We will build a curvy two shaped structure with the blocks available. We will start in the middle with Pepsi and Starbucks where Pepsi is to the left of Starbucks. We will start off the upper half first by building a diagonal line going up to the right from Starbucks with Texaco, then Twitter. Next another diagonal line going up to the left from Twitter with Target then SRI. To the left of SRI is Nvidia. Next we make a horizontal line going right to left one space down and to the left from Nvidia with HP, then Coca-Cola, and then Adidas. With the upper half down, we can now start on the bottom half starting with Pepsi. First, there is a diagonal line going down and to the left from Pepsi comprised of these blocks: McDonalds, Esso, then BMW. Below BMW is Burger King. We build a horizontal line from left to right starting one space down and to the right from Burger King with Heineken, Mercedes-Benz, then Shell. One space up and to the right from Shell we finish our last horizontal line going left to right: Stella Artois, Toyota, then UPS. This finishes our structure of the curvy two-shaped building.

We'll create a 2. The top line has Adidas, Coca-Cola, HP, Nvidia, SRI, and Target from left to right; move Nvidia and SRI up a slot. Next, place Twitter southwest of Target. Twitter creates a southwest diagonal with Texaco and Starbucks. Place Pepsi left of Starbucks and move the same direction diagonally with McDonalds, Esso, and BMW. Once placing Burger King under BMW, head right with Heineken, Mercedes Benz, Shell, Stella, Toyota, and UPS. Move Heineken through Shell down one space.

Place Peps and McDonalds together so they are touching corners at grid center (top right of McD and bottom left of Pepsi). From Pepsi, head right with Starbucks. Four above these two are Nvidia and SRI, respectively. Place Texaco one space northeast of Starbucks, with Target two above it. Diagonally right of both is Twitter. Three spaces left of Target is HP; move left with Coca-Cola and Adidas.  Place UPS six spaces below Twitter, and head right with Toyota, Stella, and finally Burger King four spaces further. The three in the middle, from right to left, are Shell, Mercedes Benz, and Heineken, all down a space. place BMW above BK, and link to McDonalds with Esso.

Place Shell tot he right of Mercedes Benz, and keep these two centered at the bottom of the grid. Four above Mercedes Benz and five above shell are McDonalds and Pepsi. Four above these two are HP and Nvidia, respectively. From Shell, place Stella northeast and head left through Toyota and UPS. From Mercedes Benz, have Heineken to its left. Burger King, BMW, and Esso are above; move the first two over a space once the column is finished. From HP, head left with Coca-Cola and Adidas. From Nvidia and Pepsi, right with SRI and Starbucks. Starbucks moves northeast with Texaco and Twitter; Twitter links to SRI through Target.
